{{ define "gotchas-file-beads-owner" }}
## Gotchas when Filing Beads

**Temporal language inverts dependencies.** "Phase 1 blocks Phase 2" is backwards.
- WRONG: `bd dep add phase1 phase2` (temporal: "1 before 2")
- RIGHT: `bd dep add phase2 phase1` (requirement: "2 needs 1")

**Rule**: Think "X needs Y", not "X comes before Y". Verify with `bd blocked`.
{{ end }}

{{ define "handoff-owner" }}
## Handoff

When context is filling up and you have incomplete work:
- `{{ cmd }} handoff "HANDOFF: <brief>" "<context>"` — send a durable summary to
  your future self and restart cleanly

Hook and mail are both real continuation surfaces for this crew session:
- work can be routed directly onto your hook
- mail can carry durable instructions, handoff notes, and follow-up context
- if durable instructions are hooked to you, treat that hooked handoff as the
  live assignment

Use handoff when you want the next crew-session turn to resume without
reconstructing context from scratch.
